# 📁 Portfolio Website – Customization Guide

## 📂 Files
- `index.html` – All sections & structure
- `style.css` – All styling & colors
- `script.js` – Interactivity (typewriter, scroll, certificates)

---

## ✏️ How to Customize

### 1. Your Name & Info
- Open `index.html`
- Search for `Your Name` → replace with your real name
- Update `your@email.com` with your actual email
- Update `+91 XXXXXXXXXX` with your phone number
- Update `Your City, India` with your location

### 2. Profile Photo (Hero Section)
- Replace the `.hero-img-placeholder` div with:
  ```html
  <img src="photo.jpg" alt="Your Name" style="width:260px;height:260px;border-radius:50%;object-fit:cover;"/>
  ```

### 3. Social Links
- Find `<a href="#">` inside `.social-row` (GitHub, LinkedIn, Twitter)
- Replace `#` with your actual profile URLs

### 4. Skills – Update Percentages
- Find `.skill-bar-wrap` entries in `index.html`
- Change `style="--w:90%"` to your actual skill level

### 5. Education
- Update school/college names, boards, years, percentages
- Update SGPA values for each semester

### 6. Projects
- Find `.project-card` sections
- Update title, description, tags
- Replace `href="#"` with your live demo and GitHub URLs
- To add a real screenshot:
  ```html
  <img src="project1.png" alt="Project 1" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;"/>
  ```

### 7. Certificates (Easy Upload!)
- Just **click any certificate card** in the browser
- A file picker opens → select your certificate image (PNG/JPG)
- The image loads instantly!
- You can also **click the image** to zoom into fullscreen
- **Edit the title/issuer** directly by clicking on the text (it's contenteditable)

### 8. Contact Form
- Currently shows a success message (no backend)
- To actually send emails, integrate with [EmailJS](https://emailjs.com) or [Formspree](https://formspree.io)

### 9. Download CV Button
- Update the `<a href="#" download>` tag to point to your actual PDF:
  ```html
  <a href="resume.pdf" class="btn-primary" download>⬇ Download CV</a>
  ```

---

## 🎨 Color Customization (style.css)
Edit CSS variables at the top of `style.css`:
```css
--accent: #00d4ff;      /* Cyan – main accent */
--accent2: #7c3aed;     /* Purple – secondary */
--accent3: #f59e0b;     /* Amber – education badges */
--bg: #0a0e1a;          /* Main background */
--card: #141b2d;        /* Card background */
```

---

## 🚀 How to Deploy (Free)
1. **GitHub Pages**: Push to GitHub → Settings → Pages → Deploy
2. **Netlify**: Drag & drop the folder at netlify.com
3. **Vercel**: Connect GitHub repo at vercel.com

---

Built with ❤️ using HTML, CSS & JavaScript — No frameworks needed!